Content:

wikigrab.py:
    A Python script to grab an arbitrary Wiki page, either in HTML or
    XML fromat, and print it to the stdout. The script can also be used
    as a module, providing a wikigrab() function that can be used from
    other scripts to grab a Wiki page.
    Type ./wikigrab.py for futher usage info.

extract_raw_wikipage.xsl:
    A very small XSLT stylesheet to extract the raw wiki text content from
    an XML wikipage.

Typical usage:

    ./wikigrab.py http://intranet:8080/wiki clovis clovis Main_Page
    
    Extracts the Main Page in HTML from the intarnet Clovis wiki, using
    clovis/clovis as username/password.
    
    ./wikigrab.py -x http://intranet:8080/wiki clovis clovis Main_Page \
        > Engineering.xml
    
    Extracts the Engineering page as an XML document and saves it in
    Engineering.xml
    
    ./wikigrab.py -x http://intranet:8080/wiki clovis clovis Main_Page \
        | xsltproc extract_raw_wikipage.xsl - \
        > Engineering.txt
        
    This extracts the raw Wiki text content, the one you typed into the
    Wikipage in the first place.
